hiQAudSwapFrequencyAboveCritThld NOTIFICATION-TYPE
            OBJECTS { rtpEvtSequenceNumberIndex,
                      rtpEvtCurrId,
                      rtpEvtSet ,                     --102
                      rtpEvtNum ,                     --720
                      rtpEvtSeverity,
                      rtpEvtEventTime,
                      rtpEvtReportingObject,
                      rtpEvtFaultyObject,
                      rtpEvtEndkey,
                      rtpEvtFormatText,
                      rtpEvtParameters,
                      rtpEvtAlarmType,
                      rtpEvtShortText,
                      rtpEvtFilterLastTransId,
                      rtpClusterName
            }
            STATUS current
            DESCRIPTION  "The RTP Audit swap frequency detector has detected high swap out activities.
                        This may affect the system's performance and compromise your running RTP if these
                        activities continue. The average number of swapped pages per second over the last
			10 seconds is derived from /proc/vmstat (pswpout) and rounded up to the next integer.
			This alarm is raised when that value reaches a configured threshold. If the situation
			abates, an abatement will be issued during the next check cycle."
            ::= { hiQAudFaultMgt 720 }

