hiQVerySevereHardwareFailureTrap NOTIFICATION-TYPE
            OBJECTS { rtpEvtSequenceNumberIndex,
                      rtpEvtCurrId,
                      rtpEvtSet ,                     --219
                      rtpEvtNum ,                     --1
                      rtpEvtSeverity,
                      rtpEvtEventTime,
                      rtpEvtReportingObject,
                      rtpEvtFaultyObject,
                      rtpEvtEndkey,
                      rtpEvtFormatText,
                      rtpEvtParameters,
                      rtpEvtAlarmType,
                      rtpEvtShortText,
                      rtpEvtFilterLastTransId,
                      rtpClusterName
            }
            STATUS current
            DESCRIPTION  "This event is used to report a hardware-related critical alarm. Listed below are
                        the typically reported hardware alarms along with the frequency that the status of
                        each is checked: Ethernet link or Bonding Group is inactive (checked every minute),
                        RAID storage failures (checked every 5 minutes), Disk errors (checked in real-time),
                        Platform Hardware errors (Temperature, Voltage, etc) detected via IPMI sensors
                        (checked every 30 seconds)" 
            ::= { hiQHardwareFaultMgt 1 }

